These sessions aimed at orienting Approving Authorities  and PMT members to be able to:  a) identity and clarify the critical roles and responsibilities in the implementation of performance management policy in the Department; b) equip with the necessary tools, criteria and best practices for fair and effective performance reviews and evaluation;  
c) reinforce skills in conducting coaching and feedback mechanisms and professional development initiatives for performance enhancement; and 
d) understand the rationale for revising RPMS guidelines and discuss its possible key changes.

Catchup Activities Description:
The Pre-Work Session will be conducted to:
- review the applicability of external services declared in DepEd CC 2025;
- check the alignment of existing external services to QMS declared processes;
- identify new external services;
- finalize list of external services for DepEd CC 2026; and,
- write the initial draft of service charters for DepEd CC 2026.
